.TH IMGMOD-VIDFRAME 1 "July 7, 2026" "imgmod 1.4.0"
.SH NAME
imgmod-vidframe \- Extract one frame from a video
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B imgmod vidframe
[\fB-f\fR \fIFRAME\fR] [\fB-t\fR \fITIMESTAMP\fR] \fIINPUT\fR [\fIOUTPUT\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B imgmod vidframe
uses ffmpeg to extract one frame from a video as an image.

When no frame or timestamp is specified, the first frame is extracted. When
\fIOUTPUT\fR is omitted, the output path is generated from \fIINPUT\fR as
\fISTEM\fB-frame.png\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f \fIFRAME\fR
Extract a zero-based frame number.
.TP
.B \-t \fITIMESTAMP\fR
Extract a frame at an ffmpeg timestamp, such as \fB00:00:03.500\fR or
\fB3.5\fR.
.TP
.B \-h
Show usage help.
.TP
.B \-v, --version
Show the plugin name and version.
.SH OUTPUT
The command prints the output file path and reports it through
\fBimgmod_output\fR so it can be optimized by \fBimgmod -o\fR.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B ffmpeg
Video tool used to extract the frame.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Rémino Rem: <https://remino.net/>
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR imgmod (1)
